    "custom_admin_box_html": "        <!-- Extended Info Content Section -->\n        <section style=\"margin-bottom: 25px; margin-top: 35px;\">\n            <h2 style=\"color: #2c3e50; font-size: 20px; border-bottom: 1px solid #ddd; padding-bottom: 5px;\">📊 Extended Platform Insights & Technical Architecture</h2>\n            <p style=\"font-size: 15px; color: #555;\">\n                To understand how apps like Yono GoGo Rummy operate in the wild, it is essential to analyze their distribution mechanism, operational landscape, and technical profile. Below is an analytical breakdown of the extended infrastructure behind these gaming platforms.\n            </p>\n\n            <!-- Technical Summary Table -->\n            <table style=\"width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin: 20px 0; font-size: 14px; text-align: left;\">\n                <thead>\n                    <tr style=\"background-color: #343a40; color: #fff;\">\n                        <th style=\"padding: 12px; border: 1px solid #454d55;\">Metric Parameter</th>\n                        <th style=\"padding: 12px; border: 1px solid #454d55;\">Technical Status / Details</th>\n                    </tr>\n                </thead>\n                <tbody>\n                    <tr style=\"background-color: #f8f9fa;\">\n                        <td style=\"padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #dee2e6; font-weight: bold;\">Distribution Method</td>\n                        <td style=\"padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #dee2e6;\">Sideloaded APK packages via third-party mirrors and messaging networks (Telegram/WhatsApp).</td>\n                    </tr>\n                    <tr>\n                        <td style=\"padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #dee2e6; font-weight: bold;\">Domain Profiling</td>\n                        <td style=\"padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #dee2e6;\">Frequently cycles through lookalike domain names (e.g., .xyz, .top, .vip) to bypass regional ISP domain-blocking orders.</td>\n                    </tr>\n                    <tr style=\"background-color: #f8f9fa;\">\n                        <td style=\"padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #dee2e6; font-weight: bold;\">Data Permissions Requested</td>\n                        <td style=\"padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #dee2e6; font-weight: bold; color: #c0392b;\">High Risk: Often demands access to Device Storage, Phone State (IMEI), Contacts, and SMS reading.</td>\n                    </tr>\n                    <tr>\n                        <td style=\"padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #dee2e6; font-weight: bold;\">RNG Certification</td>\n                        <td style=\"padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #dee2e6;\">Unverifiable. Lacks transparent documentation from independent audit bodies (like iTech Labs or eCOGRA).</td>\n                    </tr>\n                    <tr style=\"background-color: #f8f9fa;\">\n                        <td style=\"padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #dee2e6; font-weight: bold;\">Payment Gateway Strategy</td>\n                        <td style=\"padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #dee2e6;\">Utilizes dynamic, short-lived P2P (Peer-to-Peer) UPI intent links to mask high-volume merchant gambling transactions.</td>\n                    </tr>\n                </tbody>\n            </table>\n\n            <!-- Deep Dive Subsections -->\n            <div style=\"margin-top: 20px;\">\n                <h3 style=\"color: #2c3e50; font-size: 18px;\">🛠️ App Architecture & Data Harvest Risks</h3>\n                <p style=\"font-size: 14px; color: #495057;\">\n                    Unlike mainstream applications vetted by Google's Play Protect or Apple's App Review teams, sideloaded Rummy APKs run with minimal external sandbox oversight. When an application requests <strong>SMS Reading Permissions</strong> under the guise of \"auto-reading OTPs,\" it simultaneously gains visibility into your private financial messages, transactional alerts, and personal communication data. \n                </p>\n\n                <h3 style=\"color: #2c3e50; font-size: 18px; margin-top: 20px;\">⚖️ The Jurisdictional Shell Game</h3>\n                <p style=\"font-size: 14px; color: #495057;\">\n                    Most white-label Yono clone variations operate out of murky legal jurisdictions. The customer support infrastructure is frequently hosted on external, encrypted chat networks like Telegram or WhatsApp Business accounts bound to virtual international numbers. This intentional isolation ensures that if a user suffers a massive financial loss due to a software glitch, rigid bot-play, or structural transaction denial, tracking the platform operators or holding them legally accountable becomes virtually impossible.\n                </p>\n\n                <h3 style=\"color: #2c3e50; font-size: 18px; margin-top: 20px;\">🔒 Cybersecurity Checklist for Users</h3>\n                <p style=\"font-size: 14px; color: #495057;\">\n                    If you must interact with third-party gaming packages, always deploy the following operational security countermeasures:\n                </p>\n                <ul style=\"font-size: 14px; color: #495057; padding-left: 20px;\">\n                    <li><strong>Run APK Scans:</strong> Upload any downloaded installation package to tools like <em>VirusTotal</em> prior to execution to check for trojans and embedded spyware scripts.</li>\n                    <li><strong>Revoke Runtime Permissions:</strong> Once the app is installed, navigate to your device settings and manually strip away unnecessary permissions like Location, Contacts, and Storage access.</li>\n                    <li><strong>Check for HTTPS Enforcement:</strong> Ensure all network requests made inside the app's internal WebViews route over securely encrypted protocols (`https://`) to limit middleman data snooping.</li>\n                </ul>\n            </div>\n        </section>\n",
